### Description

Hello. 

I have a problem:
---------------------------
I have my custom component. I send form: UntypedFormGroup like an Input to this component.
Component code: 

import { Component, Input } from '@angular/core';
import { UntypedFormGroup } from '@angular/forms';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-radio-buttons',
  templateUrl: './radio-buttons.component.html',
  styleUrl: './radio-buttons.component.scss'
})
export class RadioButtonsComponent {
  @Input() form: UntypedFormGroup;
  @Input() values: string[];
  @Input() formControlName: string;
}


Template code: 

@if (form && values) {
  <div class="radio-buttons-container" [formGroup]="form">
    @for (value of values; track value) {
      <div class="buttons-wrapper">
        <input
            type="radio"
            class="radio form-control"
            formControlName="{{formControlName}}"
            [id]="'radioButton' + value"
            [value]="value"
            [attr.data-test]="'radio-button-' + value">
        <label [for]="'radioButton' + value">
          {{ 'order-approve.' + value | translate }}
        </label>
      </div>
    }
  </div>
} @else {
  {{ 'order-approve.no-needed-data-provided' | translate }}
}


I have got the error (see below in error section).

In case I move template code right to the parent component, the error not appears. 

Can someone help me with that?



### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

_No response_

### Please provide the exception or error you saw

NG01050: formControlName must be used with a parent formGroup directive.  You'll want to add a formGroup
      directive and pass it an existing FormGroup instance (you can create one in your class).

    Example:


  <div [formGroup]="myGroup">
    <input formControlName="firstName">
  </div>

  In your class:

  this.myGroup = new FormGroup({
      firstName: new FormControl()
  });

